We recommended that the responsible officials and employees of the Municipality observe prudence in the discharge of their duties so that government funds are appropriately safeguarded thru the following measures:

1.	In case a Letter of Credit shall be issued by the Municipality, the BAC shall see to it that the terms in the opening of the same conform with the requirements of Section 42.6 of the Revised IRR of the R.A. No. 9184 and if the winning bidder is a local supplier, the same should be issued to the latter and not to its foreign manufacturer or supplier;

