We recommend that management strictly implement the governing rules and regulations particularly from the Municipal Tax Code and shall undertake the following measures:
a) Impose penalty and apply the civil remedies provided in the pertinent Section of the Municipal Tax Code to delinquent tenants of wet and dry market stalls and business taxpayers;
b) Conduct examination of the delinquent business taxpayers and business establishments specially on wet and dry market stalls and business tax payers to ascertain, assess and collect the true and correct amount of tax due from the taxpayer concerned;
c) Impose penalties thereon and administrative sanctions as warranted; and
d) Strengthen the municipal revenue administration including regular monitoring and imposition of penalties for delinquencies.

We recommend:
a) Require the concerned Administrative official to have a serially numbered Driver’s Trip Ticket and have it duly approved and properly filled-up as to plate number of the vehicle, and the details of the balances of gasoline, beginning, additions and ending and to determine the number of liters of the gasoline to be loaded based on the distance in kilometers on the supposed trip or scope of work to be done on any undertaking to be accomplished;
b) The Supply Officer or his/her authorized representative together with the inspection committee shall witness the reading of the beginning balance of the gasoline contained in the tank before loading the determined number of liters per approved withdrawal of gasoline duly signed as inspected;
c) At the end of the trip or undertaking the concerned Driver shall indicate the number of liters of gasoline used and the balance in liters remaining in the tank which would serve as the beginning balance on the next trip or undertaking;
d) At the end of the month the Supply Officer shall submit a Monthly Summary of Fuel Consumption for each government vehicle owned by the LGU.

To resolve this observation, we are recommending the following action to be undertaken by management immediately;

Create a committee to work on the titling of the acquired lots and to undertake measures necessary to hasten the documentation for the absolute ownership of the LGU. 

Set aside budget for the processing of its certificate of title as proof of ownership over the lots acquired.
